TheAkshaT
Wed Jul 14, 2004 10:32 am

Re: Puzzle !
-----------------------------------
Here's one from me:
There are 3 students A, B and C sitting in a circle. The teacher has 5 dots(sort of bindis) with her, 3 white ones and 2 black. The teacher asks all of them to close their eyes and then she sticks one white dot each to each of their foreheads. Now they are asked to open their eyes. 
They are sitting such that all of them face each other. Each one can watch the dots on the other two's foreheads but not on their own. Neither are they allowed to know of the color of the dots the teacher is left out with. 
Now if they are to prove themselves clever they are to say the color of the dot on their own forehead. After a while one of them(let's say B) proves herself clever by being able to rightly ans the color of her dot, i.e. white. The ques is what was the train of her thought? How could she logically arrive to that conclusion?

See,
1. if two of them had black dots the third one will know that he has white instantly
2. if any one of them had a black dot at head, then the other two should have concluded togethar after some time...(coz they will wait for the other white dot to conclude...) as if the case is 1 the other white dot will conclude instantly else he will wait....
3. if all of them have white, then they will take more time....as all of them will think that case may be 2....and after some time...they will realize everyone has white....

-Akshat

PS : The prerequisite for the occurance of the solution is that not only B but all have to be clever enough to realize this solution :mg:

