luckynawabs
Fri Jul 16, 2004 3:16 pm


-----------------------------------
monkey problem
1. The gravitational force acts only in the vertical direction
2. Acceleration due to gravity is the same for both monkey and bullet

So, in the vertical direction, monkey and bullet fall by the same
amount in the same time (for the bullet the falling is superimposed
on the straight line trajectory it would have taken had there not
been any gravity) and the bullet therefore hit the monkey.

