Ans for 
Suppose I hav a cheque in my name that is worth x rupees and y 
paisa (1 rupee = 100 paisa ), the banker by mistake gives me y 
rupees and x paisa  instead , on my way back , I give 5 paisa to a 
beggar , and find that the net amount in my  hand is exactly double 
of the amount on cheque (that is 2x rupees and 2y paisa) , the 
question is to find the value of x and y , without using trial and 
error , that is , a straight method, is such a method  possible?  

there r 2 cases u hav to consider : y<50 and y>=50

 

for 1st case the set of eq give ve soln.

For 2nd case the eqns r:

Y = 2X + 1        (rupees eqn)

2y -100 = x - 5    (paisa eqn )

solvin u get , x=31 , y=63

