These are some puzzles from shakuntala devi which I wasnt able to solve as well as unable to understand the solution,maybe I am missing some easy trick.Please show the detailed steps for solving the following probs.

1A,B,C,D,E,F and G  are supposed to play a game,in which the player who wins the game is supposed to give the players just as much money as they had already in their pockets.
They all palyed seven games and strangely,each won a game in turn in the order in which their names are given.But what was more strange was that when they had finished the game each of the seven had exactly the same amount,Rs 32 in his his pocket.
Can you find out how much money each person had with him before they began the game.

2.I entered a store and spent one-half of the money that was in my purse.When I came out I found that I had just as many paise as I had rupees and half as many rupees as I had paise when I went in.
How much money did I have with me when I entered?

