Rajagopal
Tue Jul 20, 2004 8:25 am

Re: Puzzle !
-----------------------------------
2.I entered a store and spent one-half of the money that was in my purse.When I came out I found that I had just as many paise as I had rupees and half as many rupees as I had paise when I went in. 
How much money did I have with me when I entered?

there is no unique ans as it is a ratio prop prob how ever to find min ans find the eqution
here it is

(100x+y)/2=x+50y where x is the no of Rs and y the no of paise
solvin we get

98x=99y hence the min such val as x&y r relatively prime r 99,98

hence ans is 99rs 98 paise

the first prob can be solved using back propagation or bottom up principle though very time cons so not solving

