flber
Thu Jul 22, 2004 11:29 pm

Re: Puzzle !
-----------------------------------

 
 You have 13 balls,all of the same size and color. One of the 13 balls is of abnormal weight ( either light or heavier). You do not know which one. In max 3 weighings, how can you tell which ball is of abnormal weight. Also you do not know the weight of each ball. 

*** You cannot find out the ball in 3 weighings unless you are given a ball which can be used for reference. This can be proven mathematically. 


 yup u can..

 Divide the 13 balls into 2 sets of 6 each and weigh them against each other

 There are 2 possibilities:
 
 1) One of the set is heavier which means tht set has the abnormal ball .... so divide the set with the abnormal ball into 2 sets again this time 3 balls in each set and weigh them against each other

  2) The sets are equal in weight and thus the 13th ball which doesnt take part in the weighing is the abnormal ball

  1A)  if the ab. ball is in one of the sets divide that set into 2 sets of 3 balls each and weigh them against each other .. continue the same way by sub-dividin into 2 sets of 1 ball each ....

 thus in atmost 3 weighings the odd ball can be found

 There is a general formula for this if sumone cud highlight it...

