khyati
Fri Jul 23, 2004 1:43 pm

Re: Puzzle !
-----------------------------------
You have 13 balls,all of the same size and color. One of the 13 balls is of abnormal weight ( either light or heavier). You do not know which one. In max 3 weighings, how can you tell which ball is of abnormal weight. Also you do not know the weight of each ball. 

divide the balls in to groups of 4,4,5 balls each
weight 4,4 groups

case 1:The sets are equal in weight  
1a)thus the abnormal ball lies in the group of 5
1b)weight 3 correct balls in one pan n 3 from the group of 5 balls. 
->if the scale tilts then the fake ball is among the 3 and u'll get to know if its heavier or lighter
put 1 ball from those 3 balls in each pan. if they balance, the abnormal is the one left out . or if the scale tilts,  the fake ball is the heavier one or the lighter one as the case may be.
--> if the scales do not tilt then the fake ball is among the 2 balls left out 
 put then one each on the pan, n find out 

case 2: the scales tilt. 

put 2 balls from the heavier side and 1 ball from lighter side in each pan, and weight them.
--> if the scale doesnt tilt,the abnormal ball is out the two left out lighter balls. weight them n find out 
-->if the scale tilts,the abnormal ball is the heavy one on the heavy side or the light one on the light side. 
find that out by measuring the two heavy balls, if they balance , the abnormal ball is the lighter ball on the lighter side
if they tilt, then abnormal ball is the heavier of the two heavy ball

whew !! it was a good one

-----------------------------------
