great_one
Thu Jul 29, 2004 7:42 pm

Re: Puzzle !
-----------------------------------
Hi,

Formula to find out if you can find the odd ball in a given set of balls :

If n weighings are allowed, we can find the odd ball among (3^n - 3)/2 identical balls.

So, for 3 weighings, the maximum number of balls can be 12. If you want to add another ball to the set, you require a reference ball. 
So, if you have a reference ball, in n weighings, we can find the odd ball from a set of ((3^n - 3)/2) + 1 balls.

You can check this formula for other combinations of these type of problems.

So, the solution will not be possible without the reference ball.

I will post the proof later. 

Regards

